        * Sets all properties of a InnerPSmiles object.
        Parameters:
        anInputStructure - An input structure (may be a monomer)
        anAvailableParticles - Hashmap of available particles
        anIsMonomer - True: anInputStructure is a monomer, false: Otherwise (default: false)
        aStartIndex - First particle number in the PSmiles matrix (default: 1)
        aFirstParticles - Cartesian coordinate of a single first particle
        aLastParticles - Cartesian coordinate of a single last particle
        aBondLength - User defined bond length for all connections between particles

      • getHeuristicDiameter

        public int[] getHeuristicDiameter()
        Determines a heuristic diameter. This algorithm choose an arbitrary start particle s. The particle (v) at the farthest from s is then traced. Depth First Search Algorithm (DFS) is used. Again, from v DFS is used to find the particle (w) at the farthest of v. This algorithm get the correct diameter, if the structure is not cyclic. To find the real diameter all possible shortest path between terminal particles have to determined. The longest of them is the diameter. This will take too much computing time by structures with many particles.
        Returns:
        Array of particles from v-particle to w-particle.

      • getPathStartToEnd

        public int[] getPathStartToEnd()
